t validation. I've successfully implemented checks for authentication and form data integrity, including null checks for the file and `client_id` fields. I'm verifying the caller's role and matching against the client ID, as well, for proper scoping. I'm now implementing the file upload processing logic.\n\n\n\n**Analyzing File Upload Details**\n\nI'm now extracting various metadata from the file upload form. Specifically, I'm parsing and sanitizing fields such as `project_id`, `title`, `document_type`, `version`, `visibility`, and `description`. I am also computing file size in kilobytes and megabytes, converting the file content to a buffer, and storing that buffer. Finally, I'm preparing to store this information, with the file itself, in an object store.\n\n\n**Storing File Uploads**\n\nI'm now implementing the local storage write, writing to multiple paths based on client IDs and alternative client IDs. The function writes files to the mock S3 on disk. This involves creating directories if needed and writing the file buffer. Then, I am storing metadata related to the new file upload in DynamoDB.\n\n\n\n**Finalizing Data Storage**\n\nI've just finished writing the data to DynamoDB. I'm storing critical metadata alongside the file in an object store. I'm taking the `client_id`, `project_id`, `title`, `document_type`, `version`, `visibility`, and `description` to create a `newDoc` object with additional properties like `sha256_hash`, `client_name`, `owner`, `status`, `lastUpdated`, `s3_uri`, and `governanceChecks`. I'm using `getNormalizedClientName` for the client name. I'm also ensuring that the \"alternative\" document entries are made to match up with our requirements.\n\n\n"}}
{"ts":"2026-06-27T22:11:50.810Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_start","contentType":"tool","toolName":"editor","toolCallId":"87vb4x9c","input":{"path":"/Users/ayushbansal/Documents/GitHub/hirezapp_landing_page/app/api/v1/documents/upload/route.ts","new_text":"import { NextResponse } from \"next/server\";\nimport crypto from \"crypto\";\nimport fs from \"fs\";\nimport path from \"path\";\nimport { \n  API_MOCK_USERS, \n  verifyJwt, \n  MockUserDbEntry, \n  getClientIdFromAssociation,\n  getNextDocumentId,\n  getClientNameFromId\n} from \"@/lib/api-auth\";\nimport {\n  dynamoDbPutPortalItem,\n  getUserFromDynamoDB,\n  mapDynamoUserToApiUser\n} from \"@/lib/dynamodb-client\";\n\nexport const runtime = \"nodejs\";\n\nfunction getAlternativeClientId(id: string): string {\n  if (id === \"client-001\") return \"1\";\n  if (id === \"1\") return \"client-001\";\n  if (id === \"client-002\") return \"2\";\n  if (id === \"2\") return \"client-002\";\n  if (id === \"client-003\") return \"3\";\n  if (id === \"3\") return \"client-003\";\n  if (id === \"client-004\") return \"4\";\n  if (id === \"4\") return \"client-004\";\n  return \"\";\n}\n\nfunction getNormalizedClientName(clientId: string): string {\n  let cid = clientId;\n  if (cid === \"1\") cid = \"client-001\";\n  if (cid === \"2\") cid = \"client-002\";\n  if (cid === \"3\") cid = \"client-003\";\n  if (cid === \"4\") cid = \"client-004\";\n  return getClientNameFromId(cid);\n}\n\nasync function getAuthCaller(req: Request) {\n  const auth = req.headers.get(\"authorization\");\n  if (!auth?.startsWith(\"Bearer \")) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Missing/malformed Authorization header.\" };\n  }\n  const decoded = verifyJwt(auth.substring(7));\n  if (!decoded?.email) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Invalid/expired access token.\" };\n  }\n  const email = decoded.email.toLowerCase().trim();\n  const dbUser = await getUserFromDynamoDB(email);\n  if (dbUser) {\n    const apiUser = mapDynamoUserToApiUser(dbUser);\n    if (apiUser.status === \"inactive\") {\n      return { status: 403, error: \"Forbidden\", msg: \"This account is inactive.\" };\n    }\n    return { caller: apiUser };\n  }\n  const user = (API_MOCK_USERS as Record<string, MockUserDbEntry>)[email];\n  if (!user) {\n    return { status: 401, error: \"Unauthorized\", msg: \"Authorized user not found.\" };\n  }\n  if (user.status === \"inactive\") {\n    return { status: 403, error: \"Forbidden\", msg: \"This account is inactive.\" };\n  }\n  return { caller: user };\n}\n\nexport async function POST(req: Request) {\n  try {\n    const auth = await getAuthCaller(req);\n    if (\"status\" in auth) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: auth.error, message: auth.msg }, { status: auth.status });\n    }\n    const { caller } = auth;\n\n    const formData = await req.formData().catch(() => null);\n    if (!formData) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Invalid form data.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const file = formData.get(\"file\") as File | null;\n    if (!file) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing file asset.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const clientIdRaw = formData.get(\"client_id\") as string | null;\n    if (!clientIdRaw) {\n      return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Bad Request\", message: \"Missing client_id.\" }, { status: 400 });\n    }\n\n    const client_id = clientIdRaw.trim();\n\n    // Scoping validation\n    if (caller.role !== \"gff_admin\") {\n      const callerClientId = getClientIdFromAssociation(caller.clientAssociation);\n      if (client_id !== callerClientId && getAlternativeClientId(client_id) !== callerClientId) {\n        return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Forbidden\", message: \"Permission denied for this client scope.\" }, { status: 403 });\n      }\n    }\n\n    const project_id = (formData.get(\"project_id\") as string || \"\").trim();\n    const title = (formData.get(\"title\") as string || file.name).trim();\n    const document_type = (formData.get(\"document_type\") as string || \"PDF\").trim();\n    const version = (formData.get(\"version\") as string || \"1.0.0\").trim();\n    const visibility = (formData.get(\"visibility\") as string || \"private\").trim();\n    const description = (formData.get(\"description\") as string || \"\").trim();\n\n    // Read file bytes\n    const arrayBuffer = await file.arrayBuffer();\n    const buffer = Buffer.from(arrayBuffer);\n\n    // Compute size string\n    const size_kb = buffer.length / 1024;\n    let fileSizeStr = \"\";\n    if (size_kb > 1024) {\n      fileSizeStr = `${(size_kb / 1024).toFixed(1)} MB`;\n    } else {\n      fileSizeStr = `${size_kb.toFixed(1)} KB`;\n    }\n\n    // Compute SHA-256 for cryptographic sealing\n    const sha256_hash = `0x${crypto.createHash(\"sha256\").update(buffer).digest(\"hex\").toUpperCase()}`;\n\n    // Get next document ID\n    const newDocId = getNextDocumentId();\n\n    // 1. Save file to mock S3 storage on local disk\n    const baseLocalS3 = path.join(process.cwd(), \"backend\", \"local_s3_storage\");\n    const writeToPath = (cid: string) => {\n      const uploadDir = path.join(baseLocalS3, cid, \"documents\", newDocId);\n      fs.mkdirSync(uploadDir, { recursive: true });\n      const filePath = path.join(uploadDir, file.name);\n      fs.writeFileSync(filePath, buffer);\n    };\n\n    writeToPath(client_id);\n    const alt_client_id = getAlternativeClientId(client_id);\n    if (alt_client_id) {\n      writeToPath(alt_client_id);\n    }\n\n    // 2. Save metadata in DynamoDB (or mock memory store)\n    const newDoc: any = {\n      id: newDocId,\n      title: title,\n      filename: file.name,\n      fileSize: fileSizeStr,\n      type: document_type,\n      document_type: document_type,\n      sha256: sha256_hash,\n      client_id: client_id,\n      client_name: getNormalizedClientName(client_id),\n      projectId: project_id,\n      project_id: project_id,\n      status: \"active\",\n      owner: caller.name || \"Dr. Sarah Vance\",\n      version: version,\n      lastUpdated: new Date().toISOString(),\n      description: description || \"Cryptographically secured enclave system documentation.\",\n      visibility: visibility === \"public\" ? \"LEVEL_I (Client View)\" : \"LEVEL_IV (Restricted)\",\n      s3_uri: `s3://gff-ai-documents-bucket/clients/${client_id}/documents/${newDocId}/${file.name}`,\n      governanceChecks: []\n    };\n\n    await dynamoDbPutPortalItem(\"DOCUMENT\", client_id, newDoc);\n    if (alt_client_id) {\n      const altDoc = { \n        ...newDoc, \n        client_id: alt_client_id, \n        client_name: getNormalizedClientName(alt_client_id),\n        s3_uri: `s3://gff-ai-documents-bucket/clients/${alt_client_id}/documents/${newDocId}/${file.name}`\n      };\n      await dynamoDbPutPortalItem(\"DOCUMENT\", alt_client_id, altDoc);\n    }\n\n    return NextResponse.json({\n      success: true,\n      message: \"Document uploaded successfully.\",\n      document: newDoc\n    }, { status: 201 });\n\n  } catch (error: any) {\n    console.error(\"Document upload error:\", error);\n    return NextResponse.json({ success: false, error: \"Internal Server Error\", message: \"An unexpected error occurred during document ingestion.\" }, { status: 500 });\n  }\n}"}}}
